{
  "stem": "3341.2",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "If there will be any danger for you, you can always resign, which was not possible.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "Anyhow, it came to the fact that both women were named trustees of the firm.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "On that day, when we got notification officially, my father was dismissed of being the owner and the managing director.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "And my brother, with a lot of pushing, was able to be like a trustee in the firm, like helping the new managers.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It ?] was in 1939.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "When the start of the Jewish persecution-- from '39 to '41-- we were able to juggle our survival.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Mind you, that-- that first transport from Slovakia started, in seriousness, in '41 and '42. '42 was already a very serious year.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They took, I remember, my wife's sister.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "One day they declared-- we had a Jewish, like a head office for Jewish affairs, consisting of twelve Jewish prominent citizens.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That was the Judenrat, in German, all right?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they-- whenever they had-- the Germans, whenever they wanted to do something against the Jews, they declared-- through the Jewish-- how would say 'rat'?",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Jewish council.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Jewish Council.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Through the Jewish council, they introduced this and that, against Jewish laws, you know, in a nice, slow way.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So the Jewish council one day declared, tomorrow morning we need 1,000 young girls, starting from 16 years of age, and 1,000 young boys.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they will go to Poland for work.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Please come tomorrow at seven o'clock, in such and such a place.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And it was all done with trickery, when the Jews are calling their own people-- have two pairs of boots, and have this and that blanket.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It sounded very, very real.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
